{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01EgESP3oKxoXtwFqgcyFYdc","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The issue is in the status test: when I do `vi.clearAllMocks()` inside the test, it clears the mock, but the `beforeEach` has already set up the mock. The problem is that when I use `vi.clearAllMocks()` inside the failure tests, it clears the mock before setting up the new rejection value. But the issue is `mockResolvedValueOnce` - it stacks values. After clearing in the failure tests, I set up `mockRejectedValue`, but since `mockQuery` was still set with `.mockResolvedValueOnce` from `beforeEach`, the once values were used before the rejection.\n\n\nActually, I think I see it now. The `beforeEach` sets up two resolved values, then `afterEach` clears everything. When the failure test runs, `beforeEach` runs again and sets up those same resolved values. I'm calling `vi.clearAllMocks()` after that to wipe them out, then setting `mockRejectedValue`. But the test is returning 200 instead of 500, which suggests the mock isn't actually rejecting.\n\nLooking at the vitest documentation, `clearAllMocks()` only clears call history and results—it doesn't reset the mock implementation itself. So those `mockResolvedValueOnce` values are still queued up. When I call `clearAllMocks()` in the test, it doesn't actually remove them from the queue, which means the first call still resolves with the queued value instead of hitting my `mockRejectedValue`.\n\nSince `Promise.all` in the status route calls `mockQuery` twice, both calls consume the queued `mockResolvedValueOnce` values before the default `mockRejectedValue` ever gets a chance to run. The fix is to use `vi.resetAllMocks()` instead, which actually clears the once-queues and resets the implementation, so I can properly set up the rejection behavior for the failure tests. I need to reset the mocks within each failure test before setting up the rejection, so the once-values from `beforeEach` don't interfere with the new mock behavior.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":896,"cache_read_input_tokens":46019,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":896},"output_tokens":9,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"154b1bb3-2180-48a3-9fc4-525491cd885a","uuid":"17819de8-f28d-4e40-a679-7354b715d2f2"}
